The paper discusses visual representations and their relationship to feature descriptors commonly used in computer vision and convolutional neural networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the complexity of the representations, which suggests a possible connection to machine learning and optimization, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely categories as well. The paper also discusses invariance, which is a common topic in neural networks and deep learning, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a possible category. Finally, the paper discusses analytical expressions, which suggests a possible connection to information theory, making cs.IT (Information Theory) a possible category as well.
